{
  "stem": "17299.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 94.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't expect a picnic, but we had not heard of any killing, nothing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything was-- we were cut off from the world.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nothing-- we even didn't know what was going on in Poland or any country of killing or nothing at that time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, the first thing we saw in the morning when we opened windows that we had guards who were marching along the train.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were Latvians.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were in khaki uniform.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had armbands with a skull and crossbones and a number, and rifles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were told nobody can get out of the train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Otherwise, you will be shot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "After a while, some Germans arrived-- a Sturmbannfuhrer, or major, and Obersturmfuhrer, which is captain, some Untersturmfuhrer, which are lieutenants, and some NCOs, which was the reception committee.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then somebody had a bullhorn and announced that we are in a foreign country now.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We are not allowed to have any money or postage stamps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And therefore two Jews had to go along the train and had to give any money-- we were allowed to take 10 marks along-- put in a hat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At the same time, we were told anyone who did not follow the orders would be shot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, we have no other choice than follow the orders.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Since he was a member of the German army before, he knew what it was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So then after they had collected the money and the postage stamps and everything, we got told to get out of the train.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One Jew got out of the train and lit a cigar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When the Germans saw that, an SS Obersturmfuhrer-- or captain, I think-- walked up to him and beat him up with a cane.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His name was Emil Mayer.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
